# Deployment secrets — NEVER commit.
# This is a belt-and-suspenders guard; the top-level .gitignore also blocks *.secret.
*.secret

# Env confs are per-site (admin URLs, node names, SANs with real IPs) — never
# commit. The repo ships only *.conf.example templates: copy one to <env>.conf
# and edit.
*.conf

# Keep committed templates.
!*.secret.example
!*.conf.example
